objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of atezolizumab plus paclitaxel compared with placebo plus paclitaxel in patients with inoperable locally advanced or metastatic TNBC

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective - Overall Survival
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of atezolizumab plus paclitaxel compared with placebo plus paclitaxel as measured by Overall Survival

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective - Patient Reported Outcomes
objectives.text: To evaluate the time to deterioration in Global Health Status

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective - Duration of Response
objectives.text: To evaluate Duration of Objective Response

objectives.name: Exploratory Patient-Reported Outcomes Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate changes from baseline in patient function and symptoms (EORTC QLQ C30 and QLQ BR23)

objectives.name: Exploratory Quality of Life Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate changes from baseline in overall health and quality of life (EORTC QLQ C30, Items 29 and 30)

endpoints.name: Primary Efficacy Endpoint
endpoints.text: Progression-free survival (PFS), defined as the time from randomisation to the first occurrence of disease progression, as determined by the investigator using RECIST v1.1, or death from any cause during the study, whichever occurs first.

endpoints.name: Secondary Endpoint: Time to deterioration in Global Health Status
endpoints.text: Time to deterioration in Global Health Status

endpoints.name: Secondary Endpoint: Duration of Objective Response
Exploratory Endpoint: Changes from Baseline in Patient Function and Symptoms
endpoints.text: Changes from baseline in patient function and symptoms (EORTC QLQ C30 and QLQ BR23)

endpoints.name: Exploratory Endpoint: Changes from Baseline in Overall Health and Quality of Life
endpoints.text: Changes from baseline in overall health and quality of life (EORTC QLQ C30, Items 29 and 30)

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand - PD-L1 Positive Subpopulation
estimands.populationSummary: Adult patients with inoperable locally advanced or metastatic TNBC whose PD-L1 status is IC1/2/3 at the time of randomisation Summary measure: Hazard ratio from a stratified Cox regression model.

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Discontinuation of atezolizumab/placebo or paclitaxel due to toxicity or other reasons prior to progression

intercurrentEvents.name: Missing tumor assessments
intercurrentEvents.text: Patient missed two or more scheduled assessments immediately prior to the PFS event
